A mattress manufacturing firm, Mouka Limited, has restated its commitment to adding value to life and sustaining partnership with the Lagos State government as the company celebrated with families of babies born on 2022 New Year’s Day in Lagos. According to a statement by the company, Mouka presented gifts to mothers of the first babies at the Harvey Road Health Centre and Maternity, Yaba, Lagos Mainland; Onikan Health Centre; and Lagos Island Maternity Centre, among others. It said items presented by the company at the event included Dreamtime Baby mattress, Mouka baby mat, baby wipes and diapers. Speaking at the event, the wife of the Lagos State Governor, Dr Ibijoke Sanwo-Olu, commended the company for its “consistency in adding value to life through quality sleep”. Other personalities at the event included the Lagos State Commissioner for Health, Prof. Akin Abayomi, and the Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer, Harvey Health Centre and Maternity, Dr Yetunde Sotunde. Commenting on the initiative, the Brand Manager, Mouka, Yemisi Obadina, said, “The priority of Mouka is to continually advocate a healthy sleep culture, especially for children. The Mouka Dreamtime mattresses are specially designed with children in mind.” According to him, the Dreamtime mattress is water-resistant, yet breathable to keep the body cool, as it is also made with the right density of foam to keep children comfortable while they sleep. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com